The paper focuses on computer vision tasks, specifically Visual Question Answering (VQA), which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses deep neural networks, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The study of accuracy and robustness of VQA models involves machine learning techniques, which is covered by cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the use of semantically relevant questions, which falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper deals with large-scale datasets, which is covered by cs.MM (Multimedia).
